---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import BaseHead from "../../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="Gelatin Reference Articles | gelatincalculator.com"
      description="Plain-English guides on gelatin bloom strength, sheet-to-powder conversion, and how much gelatin to use per cup of liquid."
      path="/articles/"
    />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-stone-900">
    <nav class="border-b border-stone-200">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/" class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900">gelatincalculator.com</a>
        <div class="flex gap-5 text-sm text-stone-600">
          <a href="/about" class="hover:text-amber-700">About</a>
          <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-amber-700">Privacy</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-3">Articles</h1>
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-12">Reference guides for working with gelatin</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <a href="/what-is-gelatin-bloom-strength/" class="block border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">What Is Gelatin Bloom Strength?</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Bloom strength measures how firmly gelatin sets. Here's how the Bloom test works,
            what the grade scale means (bronze through platinum), and why the number matters
            when substituting one gelatin for another.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/gelatin-sheets-vs-powder/" class="block border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Gelatin Sheets vs Powder: What's the Difference?</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Sheets and powder are chemically the same, but they're measured differently and have
            different bloom strengths. This page covers the grade comparison table, when each
            format is used, and the conversion math.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/how-much-gelatin-per-cup-of-liquid/" class="block border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">How Much Gelatin Per Cup of Liquid?</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Reference ratios by desired texture — soft set through very firm — plus the
            variables that change how much you need: acid, sugar, dairy, proteolytic
            enzymes, and temperature.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/what-is-bloom-strength/" class="block border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Gelatin Bloom Strength — Plain-English Guide</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Which bloom strength to use for panna cotta, gummy bears, mirror glaze, and
            stabilized whipped cream. Includes a grade table and worked conversion examples.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/sheets-to-powder/" class="block border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 hover:border-amber-300 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Gelatin Sheets to Powder Conversion</p>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Convert any sheet grade (bronze, silver, gold, platinum) to grams of powder,
            accounting for both bloom strength and sheet weight. Includes common conversion
            scenarios.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 p-5 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl">
        <p class="font-medium text-stone-900 mb-2">Not sure what bloom strength your gelatin is?</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          The main calculator starts with a diagnostic step — answer a few questions about
          your gelatin and it identifies the likely bloom value before running the conversion.
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="text-amber-700 underline underline-offset-4 text-sm hover:text-amber-600">
          Go to the calculator →
        </a>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
